Comedian Rory McGrath has been arrested on suspicion of carrying out an attack following a 'drunken row' in his hometown.

McGrath, 57, was held after police were called to a house in Pool, near Redruth, in Cornwall, last Friday.

It is alleged the 'Three Men in a Boat' star attacked a man and a woman who tried to help him while he was 'heavily in drink'.

