'A man in his late 40s received a bloody nose and scratches to the face. A 57-year-old man from the Cambridge area was arrested on suspicion of common assault and ABH assault. He was later bailed until July 5.'

McGrath was educated at Redruth Grammar School and went on to Emmanuel College, Cambridge.

He became a member of the Cambridge Footlights before finding fame on the Channel 4 sketch show Who Dares Wins.

Rory is also known for roles in Chelmsford 123 and as a regular panellist on They Think It's All Over.

A spokesman for the comedian said she did not know anything about the alleged incident.

